In[48]:
for col in ['balance','campaign','previous']:
    Q1=data[col].quantile(0.25)
    Q3=data[col].quantile(0.75)
    print(f"{col}")
    print("Q1 is ",Q1)
    print("Q3 is ",Q3)
    IQR=Q3-Q1
    print("IQR is " ,IQR)
    lower_limit= Q1-1.5*IQR
    upper_limit= Q3+1.5*IQR
    print("Lower_limit is " ,lower_limit)
    print("Upper_limit is ", upper_limit)
    data[col]=data[col].clip(lower_limit,upper_limit)

### Model insights 1. Logistic Regression before SMOTE showed high accuracy but failed to identify customers who subscribed. 2. After applying SMOTE, recall improved but overall performance was still moderate. 3. Random Forest performed better by capturing more potential customers. 4. Gradient Boosting showed high accuracy but missed many positive cases. 5. XGBoost achieved the best balance between precision and recall with the highest F1-score.

Final Model Selection

  1. XGBoost chosen
  2. Reason: best F1-score and recall
  3. Suitable for marketing use case

Challenges Faced

  1. Class imbalance solved using SMOTE & calss weighting
  2. High dimensionality handled via encoding
  3. Low recall initially improved using ensemble models
  4. Overfitting risk controlled using boosting parameters

Business Analytics

  1. Prioritize customers predicted as Yes
  2. Focus on customers with previous campaign success
  3. Reduce repeated calls
  4. Use model output before marketing calls
  5. Improve ROI and reduce cost
